            "body": "Hmm. I had tried `:set termguicolors` but it made things worse (so I understand why it's off by default for Apple Terminal). Is there anything I can configure in Apple Terminal to work around this? From my perspective, this worked fine in nvim 0.9.5, so it feels like a regression, and asking me to switch my whole terminal emulator feels unfortunateâ€¦\r\n\r\nI just tried downloading iTerm2, and now my neovim background is a strange blue color that both decreases contrast and clashes with the abutting window chrome. Is there a way to customize that? I assume it's intentional but it's surprising to me considering the minimalism of the rest of the colorscheme.\r\n\r\n<img width=\"697\" alt=\"Screenshot of nvim --clean in iTerm2 3.5.3 with default settings\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/9208e5cc-5e2f-4b46-97e5-b82520bbb15a\">\r\n",
